cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper discusses privacy preserving data publishing, which is a topic related to database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses techniques for protecting against membership disclosure and attribute disclosure, which are topics related to security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a new technique for data anonymization, which involves partitioning the data, and evaluates its effectiveness using workload experiments, which are topics related to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG, cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the computation of sliced data that obey the l-diversity requirement, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT).
